<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1625,1650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="gratilla" authorityName="gratilla (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[324,641,1625,1650]" class="Echinoidea" family="Toxopneustidae" genus="Tripneustes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="gratilla" subSpecies="gratilla">
<emphasis box="[324,641,1625,1650]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Tripneustes gratilla gratilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most common shallow water species found among the seagrass beds of the southern coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[579,693,1661,1686]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. The colour of the primary spines varies from orange to white.
</paragraph>
